{
  "title": "ISic003374. Funerary inscription for Athano",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\"><span data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ἀθανώ\">Ἀθανοι</span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὰ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρηστὰ</span>  <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ἀθανώ\">Ἀθανοι</span>  <span data-text=\"χρηστὰ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρηστὰ</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\"><span data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ἀθανώ\">ΑΘΑΝΟΙ</span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὰ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΑ</span><br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Ἀθανοι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Ἀθανώ\">ΑΘΑΝΟΙ</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὰ\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΑ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003374_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003374_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003374.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003374-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003374_threequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003374_threequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003374_threequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic003374_threequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><p>  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>Athano, a worthy lady, farewell!</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>The female name Ἀθανώ is attested on at least seven occasions, primarily in the eastern half of the Mediterranean according to <a href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=Ἀθανώ\" target=\"_blank\">LGPN</a></p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Orsi NSA 1920 337 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Lines 1-3  70-125  Not measured    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
